        <num>CC 2506</num>
        <heading>2506.  Rights of buyer against seller in case of eviction</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2506.  Rights of buyer against seller in case of eviction
A buyer who avails himself of the warranty against eviction may recover from the seller the price he paid, the value of any fruits he had to return to the third person who evicted him, and also other damages sustained because of the eviction with the exception of any increase in value of the thing lost.</p>
        </content>
